<h1 id="unit-1" class="unit-title">Unit 1: The Basics of the Web and HTML</h1>
  <div class="lesson">
    <h2 id=unit-1-1>Lesson 1: The World Wide Web</h2>
      <div class="content">
        <ul class="bullet">
          <li>Technological empathy is to understand what happens when you open (or create) a web page</li>
          <li>understanding how users, computers, servers, http, and the Internet all fit together</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
  </div>

<div class="lesson">
  <h2 id="unit-1-2">Lesson 2: HTML</h2>
    <div class="content">
    <ul class="bullet">
      <li>HTML stands for <em>HyperText Markup Language</em> and is the basis for almost every webpage; links between pages are called hyperlinks (links for short); invented in the ealry 1990s and has something in the order of 30bn pages</li>
      <li>Your browser makes requests via the Internet to servers. These requests are using a protocol called HTTP. And the servers respond with files that the browser displays</li>
      <li>And the protocol HTTP is just a very simple protocol that your browser uses to communicate with these servers</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="lesson">
